FBIS3-1526 "drafr062_a_94004" FBIS-AFR-94-062 Document Type:Daily Report 30 Mar 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Chad Cameroonians Reportedly Arrested in Border Area AB3003133094 Lagos Voice of Nigeria in English 1030 GMT 30 Mar 94 AB3003133094 Lagos Voice of Nigeria Language: English Article Type:BFN [From the press review] [Text] On Cameroon's expansionist move, THE VANGUARD reports that it has now engaged in a fresh border dispute with its northern neighbor, the Chad Republic, despite Cameroon's claim to Nigeria's territory, that is the Bakassi Peninsula. The paper also adds that border skirmishes were reported between Cameroon and Chadian forces. Based on this, it reports that 10 Cameroonians have been arrested by the Chadians, but THE VANGUARD did not say whether they were soldiers or civilians.
